external_knowledge:
- Gear refers to 'equipment' in the item type column;
- Success rate here means the average win rate of the items used by the players;
- Games they've played in refers to the distinct game IDs recorded for each player.

- A large number of players can be considered as more than 1000 distinct players;
- Better record of winnings implies more total victories than total defeats;
- Higher usage in winning matches means the sum of usage counts in victorious matches exceeds that in non-victorious matches.

sql:
SELECT CAST(AVG(player_level) AS INTEGER) AS average_player_level
FROM item_usage
WHERE item_id = 0 AND game_mode = 'ranked';

SELECT item_name, item_description
FROM items
WHERE price > (SELECT AVG(price) FROM items);

SELECT item_id, item_name, win_rate
FROM items
WHERE win_rate > (SELECT AVG(win_rate) FROM items);

SELECT item_id, win_rate
FROM win_rates
WHERE win_rate = (SELECT MAX(win_rate) FROM win_rates);

SELECT * 
FROM item_usage 
WHERE item_id = 'Your_Item_ID';
